#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:1
msgid "Best practices"
msgstr "最佳實踐"

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:3
msgid "URLs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:5
msgid ""
"The Nix language syntax supports bare URLs, so one could write `https://"
"example.com` instead of `\"https://example.com\"`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:7
msgid ""
"[RFC 45](https://github.com/NixOS/rfcs/pull/45) was accepted to deprecate "
"unquoted URLs and provides a number of arguments for how this feature does "
"more harm than good."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:11
msgid "Always quote URLs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:15
msgid "Recursive attribute set `rec { ... }`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:17
msgid "`rec` allows you to reference names within the same attribute set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:19 ../../../guides/best-practices.md:44
#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:95 ../../../guides/best-practices.md:203
#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:217
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "範例："

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:21
msgid ""
"rec {\n"
"  a = 1;\n"
"  b = a + 2;\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:29
msgid "{ a = 1; b = 3; }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:34
msgid ""
"A common pitfall is to introduce a hard-to-debug error `infinite recursion` "
"when shadowing a name. The simplest example for this is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:37
msgid "let a = 1; in rec { a = a; }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:42
msgid "Avoid `rec`. Use `let ... in`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:46
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  a = 1;\n"
"in {\n"
"  a = a;\n"
"  b = a + 2;\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:58
msgid "Self-reference can be achieved by explicitly naming the attribute set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:60
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  argset = {\n"
"    a = 1;\n"
"    b = argset.a + 2;\n"
"  };\n"
"in\n"
"  argset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:72
msgid "`with` scopes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:74
msgid "It's still common to see the following expression in the wild:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:76
msgid ""
"with (import <nixpkgs> {});\n"
"\n"
"# ... lots of code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:83
msgid ""
"This brings all attributes of the imported expression into scope of the "
"current expression."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:85
msgid "There are a number of problems with that approach:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:87
msgid ""
"Static analysis can't reason about the code, because it would have to "
"actually evaluate this file to see which names are in scope."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:88
msgid ""
"When more than one `with` is used, it's not clear anymore where the names "
"are coming from."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:89
msgid ""
"Scoping rules for `with` are not intuitive, see this [Nix issue for details]"
"(https://github.com/NixOS/nix/issues/490)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:92
msgid ""
"Do not use `with` at the top of a Nix file. Explicitly assign names in a "
"`let` expression."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:97
msgid ""
"let\n"
"  pkgs = import <nixpkgs> {};\n"
"  inherit (pkgs) curl jq;\n"
"in\n"
"\n"
"# ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:108
msgid ""
"Smaller scopes are usually less problematic, but can still lead to surprises "
"due to scoping rules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:111
msgid ""
"If you want to avoid `with` altogether, try replacing expressions of this "
"form"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:113
msgid "buildInputs = with pkgs; [ curl jq ];"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:118
msgid "with the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:120
msgid ""
"buildInputs = builtins.attrValues {\n"
"  inherit (pkgs) curl jq;\n"
"};"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:129
msgid "`<...>` lookup paths"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:131
msgid ""
"You will often encounter Nix language code samples that refer to `<nixpkgs>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:133
msgid ""
"`<...>` is special syntax that was [introduced in 2011] to conveniently "
"access values from the environment variable [`$NIX_PATH`]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:138
msgid ""
"This means the value of a lookup path depends on external system state. When "
"using lookup paths, the same Nix expression can produce different results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:141
msgid ""
"In most cases, `$NIX_PATH` is set to the latest channel when Nix is "
"installed, and is therefore likely to differ from machine to machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:144
msgid ""
"[Channels](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/nix-channel.html) "
"are a mechanism for referencing remote Nix expressions and retrieving their "
"latest version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:147
msgid ""
"The state of a subscribed channel is external to the Nix expressions relying "
"on it. It is not easily portable across machines. This may limit "
"reproducibility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:151
msgid ""
"For example, two developers on different machines are likely to have "
"`<nixpkgs>` point to different revisions of the {term}`Nixpkgs` repository. "
"Builds may work for one and fail for the other, causing confusion."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:155
msgid ""
"Declare dependencies explicitly using the techniques shown in [](pinning-"
"nixpkgs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:157
msgid "Do not use lookup paths, except in minimal examples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:160
msgid "Some tools expect the lookup path to be set. In that case:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:163
msgid ""
"Set `$NIX_PATH` to a known value in a central location under version control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:165
msgid "NixOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:166
msgid ""
"On NixOS, `$NIX_PATH` can be set permanently with the [`nix.nixPath`]"
"(https://search.nixos.org/options?show=nix.nixPath) option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:171
msgid "Reproducible Nixpkgs configuration"
msgstr "可重現的 Nixpkgs 組態"

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:173
msgid ""
"To quickly obtain packages for demonstration, we use the following concise "
"pattern:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:175
msgid "import <nixpkgs> {}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:179
msgid ""
"However, even when `<nixpkgs>` is replaced as shown in [](pinning-nixpkgs), "
"the result may still not be fully reproducible. This is because for "
"historical reasons the [Nixpkgs top-level expression] by default impurely "
"reads from the file system to obtain configuration parameters. Systems that "
"have the appropriate files populated may end up with different results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:185
msgid ""
"It is a well-known problem that cannot be resolved without breaking existing "
"setups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:188
msgid ""
"Explicitly set [`config`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#chap-"
"packageconfig) and [`overlays`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/"
"#chap-overlays) when importing Nixpkgs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:191
msgid "import <nixpkgs> { config = {}; overlays = []; }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:196
msgid ""
"This is what we do in our tutorials to ensure that the examples will behave "
"exactly as expected. We skip it in minimal examples to reduce distractions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:199
msgid "Updating nested attribute sets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:201
msgid ""
"The [attribute set update operator](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/"
"language/operators.html#update) merges two attribute sets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:205
msgid "{ a = 1; b = 2; } // { b = 3; c = 4; }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:210
msgid "{ a = 1; b = 3; c = 4; }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:215
msgid "However, names on the right take precedence, and updates are shallow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:219
msgid "{ a = { b = 1; }; } // { a = { c = 3; }; }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:224
msgid "{ a = { c = 3; }; }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:229
msgid ""
"Here, key `b` was completely removed, because the whole `a` value was "
"replaced."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:232
msgid ""
"Use the [`pkgs.lib.recursiveUpdate`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/"
"#function-library-lib.attrsets.recursiveUpdate) Nixpkgs function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:234
msgid ""
"let pkgs = import <nixpkgs> {}; in\n"
"pkgs.lib.recursiveUpdate { a = { b = 1; }; } { a = { c = 3;}; }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:240
msgid "{ a = { b = 1; c = 3; }; }"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:246
msgid "Reproducible source paths"
msgstr "可重現的來源路徑"

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:248
msgid ""
"let pkgs = import <nixpkgs> {}; in\n"
"\n"
"pkgs.stdenv.mkDerivation {\n"
"  name = \"foo\";\n"
"  src = ./.;\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:258
msgid ""
"If the Nix file containing this expression is in `/home/myuser/myproject`, "
"then the store path of `src` will be `/nix/store/<hash>-myproject`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:260
msgid ""
"The problem is that now your build is no longer reproducible, as it depends "
"on the parent directory name. That cannot be declared in the source code, "
"and results in an impurity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:263
msgid ""
"If someone builds the project in a directory with a different name, they "
"will get a different store path for `src` and everything that depends on it. "
"This can be the cause of needless rebuilds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:267
msgid ""
"Use [`builtins.path`](https://nix.dev/manual/nix/stable/language/builtins."
"html#builtins-path) with the `name` attribute set to something fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:269
msgid ""
"This will derive the symbolic name of the store path from `name` instead of "
"the working directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/best-practices.md:271
msgid ""
"let pkgs = import <nixpkgs> {}; in\n"
"\n"
"pkgs.stdenv.mkDerivation {\n"
"  name = \"foo\";\n"
"  src = builtins.path { path = ./.; name = \"myproject\"; };\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
